[In the past 24 hours, the USA (157 654), France (45 522), India (38 532), Brazil (35 018), and Italy (32 191) have been dominant. A global total of 11 053 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (16-17 Nov 2020).

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (14 countries) include the USA, France, India, Brazil, Italy, Russia (22 410), UK (20 051), Poland (19 152), Germany (16 206), Sweden (15 084), Iran (13 352), Spain (13 159), Ukraine (11 968), and Argentina (10 621). A total of 56 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 30 of the 56 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 9 are from the Americas region, 8 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 4 are from the South East Asia region, 3 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 are from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have increased by 4.4%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 8.5%. Looking at the same comparisons in the USA (which reported 26.5% of all newly reported cases in the past 24 hours), as the dominant country worldwide with clearly uncontrolled transmission, the 7-day change in daily reported cases is 31.1% and in reported deaths is 18.1%. In Italy, the dominant country in the European region, the 7-day change in daily reported cases is 3.0% and in reported deaths is 41.7%. And in Iran, the dominant country in the Eastern Mediterranean region, the 7-day change in daily reported cases is 29.9% and in reported deaths is 6.7%.

Impression: The global daily reported cases continue to increase. This appears to have slowed down with reduced reporting over the weekend although there is an increase today (17 Nov 2020), especially in reported deaths. as the non-reporting countries begin to report. Countries in the European and the Americas regions are still showing the largest increases in daily new case counts, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean and the South East Asia regions. The USA continues to show uncontrolled transmission. - Mod.MPP]
